Problem bEfire Try wirh resources

Problems:

❌ Lots of boilerplate code
❌ Easy to forget closing
❌ If close() throws exception → original exception is lost
❌ Resource leaks (file/db connection remains open)
----------------------------------------------------------------

#) Can you explain about try with resources?
#) How does try with resources work?

try-with-resources is a feature introduced in Java 7 that makes
 it easy to automatically close resources (like files, connections, streams, etc.) 
 after use — without needing a finally block.


 #)Try-with-resources ensures that resources like files, DB connections, streams are automatically closed after use, without needing a finally block.
#)It works only with classes that implement AutoCloseable.


try (Resource r = new Resource()) {
    // use resource
} 
// resource is automatically closed here
try (FileInputStream fis = new FileInputStream("data.txt")) {
    System.out.println(fis.read());
} 
// fis is automatically closed

----------------------------------------------------------------

import java.io.FileReader;
import java.io.IOException;

public class TryWithResourceExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        try (FileReader fr = new FileReader("test.txt")) {
            int ch;
            while ((ch = fr.read()) != -1) {
                System.out.print((char) ch);
            }
        } catch (IOException e) {
            System.out.println("Error: " + e.getMessage());
        }
        // FileReader auto-closes because it implements AutoCloseable
    }
}
----------------------------------------------------------------
How try-with-resources solves the problem?
✔ Automatically closes resources
✔ Even if exception occurs
✔ No need for finally block
✔ Prevents resource leak
✔ Cleaner code
✔ Safer exception handling